<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="692" type="key">
<keyStep pageId="2" pageNumber="692">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,220,624]" pageId="2" pageNumber="692">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="692">1 Head black dorsally, except for yellowish median and lateral carinae; abdomen extensively black, usually on basal one half or more; femora smooth, at most, with only tiny, indistinct setigerous tubercles...................................... 2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,220,624]" pageId="2" pageNumber="692">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="692">- Head brown dorsally, sometimes dark brown or black along gular area; abdomen yellowish brown, often dark brown on basal third; femora with distinct setigerous tubercles, especially near apices............................................ 3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="2" pageNumber="692">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,220,624]" pageId="2" pageNumber="692">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="692">
2 Length of setae on antennal scape and femora short, subequal to or slightly greater than diameter of segments; middle ventral margin of male genital aperture nearly flat (
<figureCitation box="[645,762,367,389]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–31" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1572,1596]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1548]" captionTargetId="figure-17@10.[151,1436,181,1548]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 17–31. Male genitalia of Metajalysus spp. M. clavatus, n. sp.: 17–20. 17, genital capsule, caudal aspect, in situ. 18, genital capsule, caudal aspect, cleared. 19, genital capsule, dorsal aspect, cleared. 20, left and right parameres. M. graziae, n. sp.: 21–23. 21, genital capsule, caudal aspect, in situ. 22, genital capsule, caudal aspect, cleared. 23, left and right parameres. M. horvathi: 24–27. 24, genital capsule, caudal aspect, in situ. 25, genital capsule, caudal aspect, cleared. 26, genital capsule, dorsal aspect, cleared. 27, left and right parameres. M. pilosus, n. sp.: 28–31. 28, genital capsule, caudal aspect, in situ. 29, genital capsule, caudal aspect, cleared. 30, genital capsule, dorsal aspect, cleared. 31, left and right parameres." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4692893" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4692893/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="692">Figs. 24, 25</figureCitation>
); distribution: 
<collectingCountry box="[902,998,367,389]" name="Argentina" pageId="2" pageNumber="692">Argentina</collectingCountry>
....................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Stusak" authorityName="Stusak" authorityYear="1977" box="[1277,1436,366,390]" class="Insecta" family="Berytidae" genus="Metajalysus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="692" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="horvathi">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1277,1436,366,390]" pageId="2" pageNumber="692">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1277,1361,366,388]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="692">horvathi</emphasis>
Štusák
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,220,624]" pageId="2" pageNumber="692">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="692">
- Length of setae on antennal scape and femora one and a half to two or more times diameter of segments; middle ventral margin of male genital aperture with sharp inverted V-shaped process (
<figureCitation box="[832,949,425,448]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–31" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1572,1596]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1548]" captionTargetId="figure-17@10.[151,1436,181,1548]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 17–31. Male genitalia of Metajalysus spp. M. clavatus, n. sp.: 17–20. 17, genital capsule, caudal aspect, in situ. 18, genital capsule, caudal aspect, cleared. 19, genital capsule, dorsal aspect, cleared. 20, left and right parameres. M. graziae, n. sp.: 21–23. 21, genital capsule, caudal aspect, in situ. 22, genital capsule, caudal aspect, cleared. 23, left and right parameres. M. horvathi: 24–27. 24, genital capsule, caudal aspect, in situ. 25, genital capsule, caudal aspect, cleared. 26, genital capsule, dorsal aspect, cleared. 27, left and right parameres. M. pilosus, n. sp.: 28–31. 28, genital capsule, caudal aspect, in situ. 29, genital capsule, caudal aspect, cleared. 30, genital capsule, dorsal aspect, cleared. 31, left and right parameres." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4692893" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4692893/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="692">Figs. 28, 29</figureCitation>
); distribution: 
<collectingCountry box="[1090,1170,425,447]" name="Ecuador" pageId="2" pageNumber="692">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
........... 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1301,1437,425,447]" pageId="2" pageNumber="692">
<taxonomicName authority="Henry &amp; Dellapé, 2021" authorityName="Henry &amp; Dellapé" authorityYear="2021" box="[1301,1370,425,447]" class="Insecta" family="Berytidae" genus="Metajalysus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="692" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pilosus" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1301,1370,425,447]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="692">pilosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1382,1437,426,447]" pageId="2" pageNumber="692" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="2" pageNumber="692">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,220,624]" pageId="2" pageNumber="692">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="692">
3 Smaller species, length 
<quantity box="[454,596,455,477]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.46" metricValueMax="3.62" metricValueMin="3.3" pageId="2" pageNumber="692" unit="mm" value="3.46" valueMax="3.62" valueMin="3.3">3.30–3.62 mm</quantity>
; pronotum with ca. 12–15 or more erect setae on either side of disc (
<figureCitation box="[1257,1349,455,477]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1729,1753]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1705]" captionTargetId="figure-17@4.[151,1436,181,1705]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Metajalysus spp. 1, M. clavatus, n. sp., male, dorsal aspect. 2, M. clavatus, male, lateral aspect. 3, M. clavatus, female, dorsal aspect. 4, M. graziae, n. sp., male, dorsal aspect. 5, M. graziae, male, lateral aspect. 6, M. graziae, female, dorsal aspect. Scale bar for plate = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4692887" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4692887/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="692">Figs. 1, 2</figureCitation>
); femora clavate apically, yellowish brown with a distinct subapical dark brown band; middle ventral margin of male genital aperture with an inverted V-shaped process (
<figureCitation box="[568,684,513,536]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–31" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1572,1596]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1548]" captionTargetId="figure-17@10.[151,1436,181,1548]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 17–31. Male genitalia of Metajalysus spp. M. clavatus, n. sp.: 17–20. 17, genital capsule, caudal aspect, in situ. 18, genital capsule, caudal aspect, cleared. 19, genital capsule, dorsal aspect, cleared. 20, left and right parameres. M. graziae, n. sp.: 21–23. 21, genital capsule, caudal aspect, in situ. 22, genital capsule, caudal aspect, cleared. 23, left and right parameres. M. horvathi: 24–27. 24, genital capsule, caudal aspect, in situ. 25, genital capsule, caudal aspect, cleared. 26, genital capsule, dorsal aspect, cleared. 27, left and right parameres. M. pilosus, n. sp.: 28–31. 28, genital capsule, caudal aspect, in situ. 29, genital capsule, caudal aspect, cleared. 30, genital capsule, dorsal aspect, cleared. 31, left and right parameres." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4692893" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4692893/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="692">Figs. 17, 18</figureCitation>
); distribution: 
<collectingCountry box="[825,921,513,535]" name="Argentina" pageId="2" pageNumber="692">Argentina</collectingCountry>
.............................. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1289,1437,513,535]" pageId="2" pageNumber="692">
<taxonomicName authority="Henry &amp; Dellapé, 2021" authorityName="Henry &amp; Dellapé" authorityYear="2021" box="[1289,1370,513,535]" class="Insecta" family="Berytidae" genus="Metajalysus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="692" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clavatus" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1289,1370,513,535]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="692">clavatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1382,1437,514,535]" pageId="2" pageNumber="692" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,220,624]" pageId="2" pageNumber="692">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="692">
- Larger species, length 4.00- 
<quantity box="[489,576,543,565]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.68" pageId="2" pageNumber="692" unit="mm" value="4.68">4.68 mm</quantity>
, pronotum with ca. 5 or 6 erect setae on either side of disc (
<figureCitation box="[1133,1223,543,565]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1729,1753]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1705]" captionTargetId="figure-17@4.[151,1436,181,1705]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Metajalysus spp. 1, M. clavatus, n. sp., male, dorsal aspect. 2, M. clavatus, male, lateral aspect. 3, M. clavatus, female, dorsal aspect. 4, M. graziae, n. sp., male, dorsal aspect. 5, M. graziae, male, lateral aspect. 6, M. graziae, female, dorsal aspect. Scale bar for plate = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4692887" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4692887/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="692">Figs. 4, 5</figureCitation>
); femora, more gradually enlarged to apex, yellowish brown to brown, with apex pale on darkest specimens; middle ventral margin of male genital aperture nearly straight across (
<figureCitation box="[528,645,601,624]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–31" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1572,1596]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1548]" captionTargetId="figure-17@10.[151,1436,181,1548]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 17–31. Male genitalia of Metajalysus spp. M. clavatus, n. sp.: 17–20. 17, genital capsule, caudal aspect, in situ. 18, genital capsule, caudal aspect, cleared. 19, genital capsule, dorsal aspect, cleared. 20, left and right parameres. M. graziae, n. sp.: 21–23. 21, genital capsule, caudal aspect, in situ. 22, genital capsule, caudal aspect, cleared. 23, left and right parameres. M. horvathi: 24–27. 24, genital capsule, caudal aspect, in situ. 25, genital capsule, caudal aspect, cleared. 26, genital capsule, dorsal aspect, cleared. 27, left and right parameres. M. pilosus, n. sp.: 28–31. 28, genital capsule, caudal aspect, in situ. 29, genital capsule, caudal aspect, cleared. 30, genital capsule, dorsal aspect, cleared. 31, left and right parameres." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4692893" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4692893/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="692">Figs. 21, 22</figureCitation>
); distribution: 
<collectingCountry box="[784,880,601,623]" name="Argentina" pageId="2" pageNumber="692">Argentina</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[927,998,601,623]" name="Bolivia" pageId="2" pageNumber="692">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
......................... 
